<paragraph id="725E36EC2499BDCFFF66D9DF1A14A3D9" blockId="135.[151,1435,1949,2014]" lastBlockId="136.[151,1436,152,292]" lastPageId="136" lastPageNumber="137" pageId="135" pageNumber="136">
<emphasis id="4095EAFE2499BDC0FF66D9DF1AFDA4B6" bold="true" box="[198,450,1949,1975]" pageId="135" pageNumber="136">Taxonomic notes:—</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="B5E14D6F2499BDC0FE62D9DF19F3A4B6" authorityName="Henderson" authorityYear="2011" box="[450,716,1949,1975]" class="Liliopsida" family="Arecaceae" genus="Geonoma" kingdom="Plantae" order="Arecales" pageId="135" pageNumber="136" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="schizocarpa">
<emphasis id="4095EAFE2499BDC0FE62D9DF19F3A4B6" box="[450,716,1949,1975]" italics="true" pageId="135" pageNumber="136">Geonoma schizocarpa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a member of the 
<taxonomicName id="B5E14D6F2499BDC0FC64D9DF1FB9A4B6" authorityName="Martius" authorityYear="1823" box="[964,1158,1949,1975]" class="Liliopsida" family="Arecaceae" genus="Geonoma" kingdom="Plantae" order="Arecales" pageId="135" pageNumber="136" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="macrostachys">
<emphasis id="4095EAFE2499BDC0FC64D9DF1FB9A4B6" box="[964,1158,1949,1975]" italics="true" pageId="135" pageNumber="136">G. macrostachys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
clade. Within this it is most closely related to 
<emphasis id="4095EAFE2499BDC0FE04D9861899A4DF" box="[420,934,1988,2014]" italics="true" pageId="135" pageNumber="136">
<taxonomicName id="B5E14D6F2499BDC0FE04D9861959A4DF" authorityName="Martius" authorityYear="1823" box="[420,614,1988,2014]" class="Liliopsida" family="Arecaceae" genus="Geonoma" kingdom="Plantae" order="Arecales" pageId="135" pageNumber="136" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="macrostachys">G. macrostachys</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="B5E14D6F2499BDC0FDD1D9861833A4DF" authorityName="Burret" authorityYear="1940" baseAuthorityName="Burret" box="[625,780,1988,2014]" class="Liliopsida" family="Arecaceae" genus="Geonoma" kingdom="Plantae" order="Arecales" pageId="135" pageNumber="136" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="multisecta">G. multisecta</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="B5E14D6F2499BDC0FCB7D9861899A4DF" authorityName="Burret (1934 a:" authorityYear="1040" box="[791,934,1988,2014]" class="Liliopsida" family="Arecaceae" genus="Geonoma" kingdom="Plantae" order="Arecales" pageId="135" pageNumber="136" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="paradoxa">G. paradoxa</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="B5E14D6F2499BDC0FC46D9861FB6A4DF" authorityName="Kunth" authorityYear="1841" box="[998,1161,1988,2014]" class="Liliopsida" family="Arecaceae" genus="Geonoma" kingdom="Plantae" order="Arecales" pageId="135" pageNumber="136" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="poiteauana">
<emphasis id="4095EAFE2499BDC0FC46D9861FB6A4DF" box="[998,1161,1988,2014]" italics="true" pageId="135" pageNumber="136">G. poiteauana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. It differs from these in its fruits surfaces which split deeply and longitudinally at maturity to reveal mesocarp with a dense layer of radial fibers.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="725E36EC2496BDCFFF66DEA71993A225" blockId="136.[151,1436,152,292]" pageId="136" pageNumber="137">
<emphasis id="4095EAFE2496BDCFFF66DEA71AC8A3FE" bold="true" box="[198,503,229,255]" pageId="136" pageNumber="137">Subspecific variation:—</emphasis>
One trait (staminate flower persistence) varies within this species. Two of 
<specimenCount id="64E7FD652496BDCFFADFDEA71A2EA225" pageId="136" pageNumber="137" type="generic">10 specimens</specimenCount>
have deciduous staminate flowers.
</paragraph>
